  "body": "# ðŸ’Ž Issue\r\n\r\nCurrently Prysm by default binds the gRPC, JSON-RPC and monitor endpoints to all available interfaces (0.0.0.0). This might cause those services to be exposed to the internet if no appropriate firewall rules are in place.\r\n\r\nIn order to decrease the available attack surface of the client those services should bind only to localhost by default. For docker based deployments where binding to 0.0.0.0 is required a `--unsafe-expose` flag could be added.\r\n",
